</form><html xmlns:xlink="http://www.w3.org/1999/xlink" xmlns:math="java.lang.Math" xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1999/xhtml" xmlns:xs="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema" xmlns:fo="http://www.w3.org/1999/XSL/Format" xmlns:fn="http://www.w3.org/2005/02/xpath-functions" xmlns:xdt="http://www.w3.org/2005/02/xpath-datatypes" xmlns:caml="http://lc.ca.gov/legalservices/schemas/caml.1#" xmlns:xhtml="http://www.w3.org/1999/xhtml"><head><title>HR74:v99#DOCUMENT</title><meta name="dc:identifier" content="HR74"/><meta name="dc:title" content="HR &#xA;              74-&#xA;                INTRODUCED&#xA;              "/><meta http-equiv="Content-Type" content="text/html;charset=utf-8"/></head><body><span class="hidden"><h2>Bill Start</h2></span><div id="bill_all" align="justify"><div id="about"><br clear="all"/><div align="center"><table style="border-collapse: collapse" cellSpacing="0" align="center" role="presentation"><tbody><tr><td align="center"/></tr></tbody></table></div><br clear="all"/><div align="center"><font size="3" style="FONT-FAMILY: MinionPC, Arial Unicode MS">
                    CALIFORNIA LEGISLATURE—
                    2025–2026 REGULAR SESSION</font></div><br clear="all"/><span id="bill_house_num"><div style="float: left; width:50%; font-weight: bold; "><span style="text-transform: uppercase; text-align:left;width:50%;"><b>
                House Resolution
              </b></span></div><div style="float:right; width:50%; text-align:right;"><span style="text-transform: uppercase;"><b>No. 74</b></span></div></span><hr/><br clear="all"/><div align="center"><table style="border-collapse: collapse" cellSpacing="0" align="center" role="presentation"><tbody><tr><td id="bill_authors" align="center"><span style="font-weight:bold;">Introduced by Assembly Member Jeff Gonzalez<br/></span></td></tr><tr><td id="bill_intro_date" align="center" class="textcenter"><br/>September 02, 2025</td></tr></tbody></table></div><hr/><br clear="all"/><div id="title"><span style="font-weight:normal;font-size:0.9em;"> Relative to Children’s Emotional Wellness Month. </span></div><br clear="all"/><br clear="all"/><div align="center"><h2>LEGISLATIVE COUNSEL'S DIGEST</h2></div><br/><div style="margin:0 0 1em 0"><span id="subject">HR 74, as introduced, Jeff Gonzalez.
                          </span></div><div><span id="digesttext"/></div><span class="hidden"><h2>Digest Key</h2></span></div><hr/><span class="hidden"><h2>Bill Text</h2></span><span class="Resolution" title="source: /caml:MeasureDoc/caml:Resolution&#xA;    "><span class="Whereas" id="id_496B9B83-C245-4CFD-9255-5293B040230A"><div style="margin:0 0 1em 0;">WHEREAS, The emotional well-being of children is foundational to their ability to learn, grow, form healthy relationships, and thrive as resilient, empowered adults; and</div></span><span class="Whereas" id="id_8906AF80-3C8E-4FEC-AE70-061B6072EC90"><div style="margin:0 0 1em 0;">WHEREAS, Thousands of children throughout California experience emotional challenges due to trauma, mental health struggles, family instability, bullying, academic pressures, and social isolation; and</div></span><span class="Whereas" id="id_04BC6A74-02E6-4200-A330-C294359C4B19"><div style="margin:0 0 1em 0;">WHEREAS, Early emotional support, education, and healing interventions can prevent long-term suffering, reduce risk of mental illness, and foster healthier, more connected communities; and</div></span><span class="Whereas" id="id_659376E0-E6BA-4F18-9909-2540B13416FD"><div style="margin:0 0 1em 0;">WHEREAS, Families, educators, caregivers, health professionals, and community leaders play a vital role in supporting children’s emotional wellness through compassion, communication, presence, and informed care; and</div></span><span class="Whereas" id="id_E8F35864-19BE-497C-9D0E-4D871171B415"><div style="margin:0 0 1em 0;">WHEREAS, We must build community and foster collaboration across sectors to strengthen emotional wellness efforts and promote awareness of valuable resources for families and individuals who can benefit from them; and</div></span><span class="Whereas" id="id_403477E2-970C-496B-840E-ED89E417B753"><div style="margin:0 0 1em 0;">WHEREAS, One of the most important tools for supporting a lifetime of financial independence and success is CalABLE, California’s savings program for people with disabilities; and</div></span><span class="Whereas" id="id_9BAAEF99-76D9-401B-80F5-7887703B3EDC"><div style="margin:0 0 1em 0;">WHEREAS, Parents are encouraged to open CalABLE accounts for their children with disabilities to save for their future while protecting their eligibility for public benefits; and</div></span><span class="Whereas" id="id_3E5C9D17-305E-4661-9A00-883154193EFD"><div style="margin:0 0 1em 0;">WHEREAS, The purple- and green-striped ribbon represents the awareness of children’s emotional wellness and the charitable goodness of people and businesses who publicly support children’s mental health and emotional wellness; and</div></span><span class="Whereas" id="id_861D109E-BC00-4B93-92DC-00E757F339D7"><div style="margin:0 0 1em 0;">WHEREAS, The Extraordinary Lives Foundation, through its unique approach to awareness, prevention, and early intervention, is effectively caring for the mental health needs of children and their families throughout California by providing an upstream approach to mental and emotional wellness; and</div></span><span class="Whereas" id="id_592568F9-3D0F-4FB4-AC33-B22B7D822831"><div style="margin:0 0 1em 0;">WHEREAS, A national month of awareness will encourage intentional reflection, education, and action to uplift the emotional needs of all children, with a focus on inclusivity, cultural sensitivity, and trauma-informed support; now, therefore, be it</div></span><span class="Resolved" id="id_424A7B4B-5010-4332-AA4B-99CE086819BD"><div style="margin:0 0 1em 0;">Resolved by the Assembly of the State of California, That the Assembly hereby proclaims the month of September as Children’s Emotional Wellness Month in the State of California and encourages all individuals, communities, schools, organizations, and government agencies to observe this month through educational programming and workshops, community healing events, school-based emotional wellness initiatives, public campaigns promoting emotional literacy and resilience, and expanded access to healing modalities and emotional support; and be it further</div></span><span class="Resolved" id="id_94A40E12-FAE8-4AA0-B88A-53CF0EE6AD9B"><div style="margin:0 0 1em 0;">Resolved, That the month of September stands as a reminder that every child deserves to feel safe, seen, and supported in their emotional journey, and may this proclamation spark lasting commitment, healing innovation, and collective care for our youngest citizens; and be it further</div></span><span class="Resolved" id="id_2CB59934-E5CD-4E5A-9B67-DF5757A386FE"><div style="margin:0 0 1em 0;">Resolved, That the Chief Clerk of the Assembly transmit copies of this resolution to the author for appropriate distribution.</div></span></span></div></body></html>
